  "texts": [
    "Input Representation and Masking.",
    "Inputs to the model are gaze data parsed into sequences of fixations, each represented by three features describing the trajectory of gaze over text: the xand y-coordinates (space) and fixation duration t (time).",
    "For preprocessing, each input sequence X ∈ R T ×F, where T denotes the number of time steps and F = 3 the number of features, is normalized to zero mean and unit variance.",
    "Normalization ensures numerical stability during training and harmonizes the distributions of real and synthetic data.",
    "During pre-training, a subset of input features is masked: a fixed proportion of the sequence is obscured, generating X masked, where partial information is visible to the model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}